			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Button elements aren&#8217;t block-level elements. I believe technically they&#8217;re &#8220;replaced in-line elements&#8221;; you can see they&#8217;re &#8220;display: inline&#8221; in Firebug or any DOM inspector.</p>
<p>SitePoint has a decent description of them. Basically browsers can get away with rendering them however they want, because there aren&#8217;t explicit specs covering them.</p>
<p><a href="http://reference.sitepoint.com/css/replacedelements" rel="nofollow">http://reference.sitepoint.com/css/replacedelements</a></p>
